// zig-zone tailnet ACL policy.
//
// Source of truth: this file. Paste into Tailscale admin → Access Controls
// when changed. The admin policy editor supports JSONC (comments).
//
// Identity model (Tailscale's, not invented here):
//   - `zig-computer` and `pico` are tagged `tag:server` — machine identities,
//     no human user behind them.
//   - `metis`, `zig`, and the iPhone are UNTAGGED — they authenticate as
//     the user's Tailscale account, so they match `autogroup:member`
//     (devices owned by a human Tailscale account).
//   - `autogroup:member` is src-only in Tailscale ACLs; `autogroup:self`
//     is the correct dst for "user's own other devices."
//
// Three rules cover the full traffic matrix:
//   1. server-to-server  (e.g. nginx → vs14-web via tailnet)
//   2. user-to-server    (SSH, Ollama API from a laptop)
//   3. user-to-self      (laptop ↔ phone over tailnet, e.g. AirDrop-style)
//
// Future contractor / co-owner devices not tied to the user's account
// match NO rule and are denied by default — allowlist-default-deny.
//
// SSH section: `check` action requires Tailscale-identity re-auth every 12h
// before opening a new SSH session. Existing sessions stay live.
//
// See spec bead `dotfiles-phe` § 4.2 for the rationale + § 6 OQs for
// decisions that shaped this.

{
  "tagOwners": {
    "tag:server": ["autogroup:admin"]
  },

  "acls": [
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["tag:server"],
      "dst": ["tag:server:*"]
    },
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["autogroup:member"],
      "dst": ["tag:server:*"]
    },
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["autogroup:member"],
      "dst": ["autogroup:self:*"]
    }
  ],

  "ssh": [
    {
      "action": "check",
      "src":    ["autogroup:member"],
      "dst":    ["tag:server"],
      "users":  ["ubuntu", "autogroup:nonroot"]
    }
  ]
}
